headline: A New Wave of Bank Mergers Is Just Getting Started

headline: Capital One sues FDIC over ‘outsized’ special assessment
summary: The McLean, Virginia-based lender said the assessment, stemming from the failures of Signature and Silicon Valley Bank, should have been $325 million, not $474.1 million.
